  "title": "Temporary Officer, Finance & Admin (Contract: 6 Months, With Option to Extend 2 Months)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Contract Duration</strong></p><p>·        6 Months (With Option to Extend 2 Months)</p><p><strong>Working Location</strong></p><p>·        City Hall</p><p><strong>Working Hours</strong></p><p>·        5 Days (Mondays to Thursdays: 8.30am to 6.00pm / 9.00am to 6.30pm; Fridays: 8.30am to 5.30pm / 9.00am to 6.00pm)<br />Lunch: 1 hour</p><p><strong>Offered Salary</strong></p><ul><li>S$4,000 per month</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>·        Background in relevant discipline such as Accounting/Finance/Business;</p><p>·        Proficient in MS Word, Excel, and PowerPoint;</p><p>·        Minimum 2 years of related working experience in similar position is preferred;</p><p>·        Knowledge of NFS@Gov system and data analytics tool is advantageous; and</p><p>·        Possess good interpersonal, communication and organizational skills;</p><p>·        Diligent with an eye for details; and</p><p>·        Able to work both independently and as a team player.</p><p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>·        Process financial transactions including payments, journals, billings and deposit records accurately and promptly, ensuring full compliance with relevant financial policies and procedures</p><p>·        Work on Financial Year End Closing matters, including preparing audit schedules and addressing auditors’ queries</p><p>·        Prepare management reports, including staff claims analysis, operating budget & overseas travel monitoring, and system access review</p><p>·        Perform procurement duties, including providing advice on compliance with procurement rules, raising of service requests in VISION and purchase orders & AOR in GeBIZ  </p><p>·        Perform travel management duties, including working with appointed travel agents to facilitate booking of air tickets & accommodation, purchase travel insurance from appointed insurance agent and activate data roaming for relevant users</p><p>·        Handle Holdings’ financial matters, including accounts preparation, audit and statutory compliance</p><p>·        Assist with other duties and ad hoc projects as assigned</p><p><br /><br />EA License No.: 96C4864</p><p>Reg No.: R1106928 TOH LAY HOON (JESSICA)</p>",
